net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.layout

Class LayoutConstraint

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.layout.LayoutConstraint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class LayoutConstraint
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    A LayoutConstraint describes where a component should be placed in a Layout.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • getWeightX

        public int getWeightX()
        Get the horizontal weight that determines how extra space is allocated to this component. The value is a percentage between 0 and 100. If the value is 100, then 100% of any extra space in the containing component will be allocated to this cell. If 0 then extra space will be allocated to other components. Values in between will assign extra space proportionally. If weight values add to more than 100%, then will be internally normalized to 100% (no modification will be made to the constraint objet iself).
        Returns:
        The horizontal weight value.

      • getWeightY

        public int getWeightY()
        Get the vertical weight that determines how extra space is allocated to this component. The value is a percentage between 0 and 100. If the value is 100, then 100% of any extra space in the containing component will be allocated to this cell. If 0 then extra space will be allocated to other components. Values in between will assign extra space proportionally. If weight values add to more than 100%, then will be internally normalized to 100% (no modification will be made to the constraint objet iself).
        Returns:
        The vertical weight value.
